history.content:
Free Registration for Attendees this Saturday (link below)

Techfair at Berkeley

December 5 - 11am-5pm

Hosted on Hopin


Hello!

We wanted to let you know about Techfair at Berkeley - MDB's annual conference for student makers!

Techfair at Berkeley is UC Berkeley's premier conference for student makers! Last year, Techfair featured 50+ student presenters with 400+ attendees. Top teams were awarded equity-free grants - and one funded team later went on to raise $500K through Kleiner Perkins & Human Capital.

This year, Techfair is going entirely virtual – and is expanding to include student makers from across all nine UC campuses! Presenters will have opportunities to showcase their projects and products, connect with other makers, and pitch their ventures to investors. Techfair will also feature some incredible keynote speakers as well as equity-free funding for top teams. The conference will be on Saturday, December 5.

Feel free to attend and check out other student projects and startups! Registration is free at https://hopin.com/events/techfair-at-berkeley/.
